{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"fo825y6yvodbes7udn8hv43","title":"Ownership-and-Borrowing","desc":"","updated":1671364199622,"created":1671363315924,"custom":{},"fname":"programing.rust.Ownership-and-Borrowing","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"ac85b1e5e77ad9c21ce42722242acfee","links":[],"anchors":{"ownership-and-borrowing":{"type":"header","text":"Ownership and Borrowing","value":"ownership-and-borrowing","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"ownership":{"type":"header","text":"Ownership","value":"ownership","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"references-and-borrowing":{"type":"header","text":"References and Borrowing","value":"references-and-borrowing","line":21,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"d81qplbgwaiawwudxe38xpf","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"ownership-and-borrowing\">Ownership-and-Borrowing<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#ownership-and-borrowing\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"ownership-and-borrowing-1\">Ownership and Borrowing<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#ownership-and-borrowing-1\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch04-01-what-is-ownership.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch04-01-what-is-ownership.html</a>\n<a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch04-02-references-and-borrowing.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch04-02-references-and-borrowing.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"ownership\">Ownership<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#ownership\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Ownership is a set of rules that govern how Rust program <strong>manage memory</strong>.</li>\n<li>Rust language checks these rules during compile time. If any of the rules are violated, the program won't compile. (Not affecting run-time)</li>\n<li>Rules\n<ul>\n<li>Each value in Rust has an owner</li>\n<li>There can only be 1 owner at a time</li>\n<li>When the owner goes out of scope, the value will be dropped.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"references-and-borrowing\">References and Borrowing<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#references-and-borrowing\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>A reference is like a pointer</strong> in that it's an address we can follow to access the data stored at that address.</li>\n<li>2 types of Rust references\n<ul>\n<li>immutable reference: <code>&#x26;T</code></li>\n<li>mutable reference: <code>&#x26;mut T</code> -> can modify the data</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Data race\n<ul>\n<li><strong>2 or more pointers</strong> access the same data at the same time</li>\n<li>At least one of the pointers is being used to <strong>write to the data</strong></li>\n<li>There's no mechanism being used to <strong>synchronize</strong> access to the data.  </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Dangling pointer: a pointer that references a location in memory that may have been <strong>given to someone else</strong>. \n<ul>\n<li>The Rust compiler guarantees: if you have a reference to some data, the compiler will ensure that the data will not go out of scope before the reference to the data does.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The rules of References\n<ul>\n<li>At any given time, you can have either <strong>one mutable</strong> reference or <strong>any number of immutable</strong> references</li>\n<li>References must <strong>always be valid</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"xfkxbponh0sohobo6pual15","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1668137379975,"created":1663481872547,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"cb44915142ec96bef8f764f3dc90389e","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-my-page":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to my page","value":"welcome-to-my-page","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"contacts":{"type":"header","text":"Contacts","value":"contacts","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"dendron":{"type":"header","text":"Dendron","value":"dendron","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["u5a2e2vvfn3x7k0shuvmb1b","qw8y69zxn8wr7tzz4gtcrrv","q7qw45jglqwmynary64q67c","6wjqcjgkrpeqtmzb1o8o1q8","3ervbn5we7t8v2l2vwtx847","4qi2z0z9fquupbd651xausx","sencgim78q74o1zuyvy1vz7","ue4oml1si982t3mmbthyxi9","zrogwjgtze8ne5joqpz8ty9","oesia0lbzh03fsoy124ck0k","el3p9zjue6h3b6zsl9oejkt","t5grkmcwvu4nl43igsj4gxz"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"# Welcome to my page\n\n- This is a place where I write my knowledge in both Vietnamese and English.\n- Please feel free to correct me if there is anything not right.\n\n## Contacts\n\n- [Github](https://github.com/thanhpp)\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/ugNRjFNqjp)\n- [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/thanhpp/)\n\n## Dendron\n\n- [Home Page](https://wiki.dendron.so/)"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true,"enableSelfContainedVaults":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":true,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"alwaysPrompt","leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2}},"randomNote":{},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelect":false},"insertNoteIndex":{"enableMarker":false},"copyNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"title"},"templateHierarchy":"template"},"workspace":{"vaults":[{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"}],"journal":{"dailyDomain":"daily","name":"journal","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd","addBehavior":"childOfDomain"},"scratch":{"name":"scratch","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd.HHmmss","addBehavior":"asOwnDomain"},"task":{"name":"task","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd","addBehavior":"asOwnDomain","statusSymbols":{"":" ","wip":"w","done":"x","assigned":"a","moved":"m","blocked":"b","delegated":"l","dropped":"d","pending":"y"},"taskCompleteStatus":["done","x"],"prioritySymbols":{"H":"high","M":"medium","L":"low"},"todoIntegration":false,"createTaskSelectionType":"selection2link"},"graph":{"zoomSpeed":1,"createStub":false},"enableAutoCreateOn